  "body": "I currently have a hardhat project with deployment and verification scripts and a submodule containing the contracts code and tests.\r\nI'd like to deploy and verify such contracts with the _hardhat-etherscan_ plugin but I get the following error:\r\n`Error in plugin @nomiclabs/hardhat-etherscan: The contract ../v1/contracts/mocks/MockERC20.sol: MockERC20 is not present in your project.`\r\n\r\nDir structure:\r\n\r\n> /\r\n> /hardhat.config.js\r\n> /v1-core/\r\n> /v1-core/contracts\r\n> /v1-core/hardhat.config.js\r\n\r\nI tried to add \r\n```\r\n  paths: {\r\n    artifacts: \"./v1/artifacts\",\r\n    cache: \"./v1/cache\",\r\n    sources: \"./v1/contracts\",\r\n    tests: \"./v1/test\",\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n  \r\n  In the root hardhat config file but the plugin still tries to compile contracts locally and fails with the aforementioned error",
